Analysis of COVID-era Apple mobility Data

Alaa Alazzeh

2021-10-10

Setup

Background and Objectives

This markdown file will use the ggplot2 (Wickham 2016) and dplyr (Wickham et al. 2021) packages to analyze the Apple maps mobility data from the time before the COVID-19 pandemic through the initial shutdowns and the continuing changes over the course of the year.

The goal will be to create a subset to a particular state, tally up the number of the cities and counties in that state with mobility data, and then to make several plots to visualize those data subsets.

The state that this document will analyze is New York.
